            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="faq-section">
                <h2 class="faq-title">Common Questions About Our Process</h2>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h4 class="faq-question">What do I need to provide to get started?</h4>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Very little initially! We just need your property address, a brief description of what you want to do, and your contact details. During the site survey, having any existing plans or deeds can be helpful but not essential.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h4 class="faq-question">Do I need to be present for the site survey?</h4>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Ideally yes, but it's not essential. We need access to measure the property, but if you can't be there, we can arrange access with a neighbor, family member, or tenant. The survey typically takes 1-2 hours.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h4 class="faq-question">Can I make changes to the drawings once they're done?</h4>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Yes, one round of revisions is included in our fee. If you want significant design changes after that, there may be an additional charge depending on the extent of the changes required.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h4 class="faq-question">What happens if my application is refused?</h4>
                    <p class="faq-answer">While rare with our 92% approval rate, if your application is refused we provide free consultation on the reasons and potential amendments. We can also handle resubmissions at a reduced cost, or assist with planning appeals if appropriate.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h4 class="faq-question">How do I pay council fees?</h4>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Council planning fees are separate from our service fees. We'll calculate the exact amount and you can either pay the council directly when we submit, or we can pay on your behalf and invoice you (whichever you prefer).</p>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h4 class="faq-question">Will you help with Building Regulations after approval?</h4>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Yes! While our core service is planning permission, we can also provide Building Regulations drawings and coordinate with structural engineers as an additional service. Many clients use us for both.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

